A RESOLUTION
1 Congratulating the Georgia Association of Manufacturers on the 125th anniversary of its
2 formation; and for other purposes.
3 WHEREAS, the Georgia Association of Manufacturers (GAM) was founded in 1900 as the
4 Georgia Industrial Association; and
5 WHEREAS, at its first annual meeting in May 1901, G. Gunby Jordan, president of the Eagle
6 and Phenix Mill in Columbus, offered a benediction, stating, "I wish this newborn
7 Association Godspeed in its mission for the financial betterment of all the institutions which
8 compose it, for the developing and cementing of closer ties of friendship . . . for the one
9 glorious purpose – the betterment of mankind"; and
10 WHEREAS, the Georgia Industrial Association became the Cotton Manufacturers of Georgia
11 in 1912 then was later renamed the Georgia Textile Manufacturers Association in 1960; and
12 WHEREAS, in 2007, the Association expanded its membership scope to represent all
13 companies engaged in manufacturing within the State of Georgia, eventually becoming
14 known as the Georgia Association of Manufacturers in 2011; and
