15 WHEREAS, from its beginning to this day, the Association has served its membership as a
16 unifying entity that has contributed substantially to the growth and development of an
17 industry of essential importance to the economic and social prosperity of this great state; and
18 WHEREAS, GAM has served and continues to serve proudly, ethically, and in a nonpartisan
19 manner as the voice of the manufacturing industry on matters of public policy at the state
20 capitol, the Georgia Public Service Commission, and other state agencies; and
21 WHEREAS, GAM also serves its growing roster of members by providing thought
22 leadership on critical issues, hosting numerous forums to discuss developments of interest
23 and best practices, creating workforce solutions, promoting modern manufacturing as a
24 compelling career choice, and providing research and intelligence to members to support
25 their success in the global marketplace; and
26 WHEREAS, Georgia is home to approximately 10,000 manufacturers who employ 435,000
27 people, including many in rural Georgia, provide jobs with above-average wages and
28 benefits, and support numerous businesses outside the manufacturing sector; and
29 WHEREAS, the manufacturing industry generated total output for the State of Georgia in
30 2023 of $77.2 billion, accounting for 9.6 percent of Georgia's total gross state product; and
31 WHEREAS, GAM continues to provide critical representation and thought leadership as
32 manufacturers and their employees help move our state into a more technologically advanced
33 future, ensuring that Georgia is a great place in which to invest in manufacturing, to work,
34 to live, and to raise our families.
